[1] New York (Erie County)
Date: Wed 10 Dec 2014
Source: WGRZ [edited]
http://www.wgrz.com/story/news/health/2014/12/09/pertussis-erie-county-november/20140395/


Erie County Health officials say they have had an "uptick" of pertussis reports, specifically on Grand Island and in East Aurora. 13 cases have been reported to the county so far for the month of November 2014. December numbers have not been tallied yet. All, except one, have been school-age children.

Grand Island Superintendent Dr Teresa Lawrence says they've had 10 cases of pertussis in the middle and high school. East Aurora is also dealing with several students with pertussis. Jerome Polakiewicz, Director of Pupil Services and Special Education say they have 8 confirmed cases, and 3 more probable cases. They have also sent a letter home to parents. The county says this is just a slight uptick and there was a more widespread outbreak in 2011 and 2012.

