[6] Michigan (Dickinson County)
Date: Tue 9 Dec 2014
Source: TV6 News [edited]
http://www.uppermichiganssource.com/news/story.aspx?id=1133826


With 7 confirmed cases of pertussis in Dickinson County it is cause for concern. Students from the county's schools are missing classes because of the illness.

The Dickinson Iron County Health Department Director Joyce Ziegler, says that the best prevention is through vaccination. "While we still may have some cases out there we don't probably have as many as we could potentially if people weren't vaccinated. So, vaccination is prevention. What that does is it protects the entire community."

[Byline: Blair Caldwell]

